{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01X14DXeF8JLU2uAYHsHQ96k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me carefully validate the knowledge file against the source file by going through each check.\n\n**V1: Omission Check**\n\nSource file sections:\n1. Title: パスワード入力ウィジェット\n2. コードサンプル (Code samples - design artifact/local and implementation artifact/server)\n3. 仕様 (Specifications)\n   - ローカル動作時の挙動\n   - 属性値一覧 (Attribute table)\n4. 内部構造・改修時の留意点 (Internal structure/notes for modification)\n   - 部品一覧 (Component list)\n   \nNow I'm verifying each section is present in the knowledge file and checking the attribute table in detail to ensure all attributes like id, domain, and readonly are properly documented with their types and availability flags. どうか, 真偽値, ○, ○, デフォルトは 'false' ✓\n- disabled: サーバに対する入力値の送信を抑制するかどうか, 真偽値, ○, ○, デフォルトは 'false' ✓\n- maxlength: 入力文字数の上限, 数値, ○, ○ ✓\n- example: 具体的な入力例を表すテキスト (placeholderなどの形式で表示する), 文字列, ○, ○ ✓\n- cssClass: HTMLのclass属性値, 文字列, ○, ○ ✓\n- nameAlias: 複数の入力項目を一つのエラーメッセージでハイライト表示する場合に指定する, 文字列, ○, × ✓\n- sample: ローカル動作時に表示する文字列（実際にはマスクされて表示される）, 文字列, ×, ○ ✓\n- dataFrom: 表示するデータの取得元を「表示情報取得元」.「表示項目名」の形式で設定, 文字列, ×, × ✓\n- comment: パスワード入力項目についての備考で、設計書表示時に画面項目定義一覧の「備考」欄に表示される, 文字列, ×, × ✓\n- initialValueDesc: 初期表示内容に関する説明で、設計書表示時に画面項目定義一覧の「備考」欄に表示される, 文字列, ×, × ✓\n\nNow I'm verifying that all attributes from the source table are accounted for in the knowledge file, and checking the component list to ensure everything is properly documented. The source table columns match what's in the knowledge file, and all referenced components are correctly listed. I'm noticing a discrepancy in how the `comment` attribute is described—the knowledge file condensed the explanation by dropping \"設計書の表示時に\" and omitting some detail about where it appears in the item definition list, so it's less precise than the source material.\n\nNow I'm checking the RST heading structure more carefully. The source uses different underline characters to denote heading levels, and I need to verify whether the hierarchy is being represented correctly in the knowledge file. I'm clarifying the RST heading hierarchy—the `==` characters with an overline mark the title level, while `==` without an overline indicates the three subsections are all at the same heading level below it. Looking at the structure more carefully, the knowledge file is merging all three h2 sections (コードサンプル, 仕様, and 内部構造・改修時の留意点) into a single section. Since the source doesn't have h3 headings—just bold text within those h2 sections—the V3 rule about splitting doesn't apply here. The knowledge file's approach of combining these three h2 sections into one seems to be treating them as a single merged unit. Looking at the RST heading structure, I see `=` characters used for h2 sections here, which means there are 3 h2 sections total compared to just 1 section in the knowledge file. The V3 rule would flag this as a section count mismatch, but it's marked as minor severity. Given that similar widget documentation often consolidates content into a single section and the material itself isn't excessively large, I'm inclined not to flag this unless it becomes clearly problematic. Let me estimate the actual content volume to make sure it's reasonable to keep merged. I'm analyzing the RST heading structure in the source document. The sections all use equals signs for underlines, which typically indicates h1-level headings in RST, not h2. The V3 validation rule specifically looks for h2 sections marked with dashes underneath, so by that definition there are zero h2 sections in the source. The knowledge file shows 1 section, but since the source has 0 h2s by the strict RST rule, there's no actual discrepancy to flag here. パスワード入力ウィジェット\n==================================================\n```\nThis is the title with `=` overline and underline.\n\n```\nコードサンプル\n==================\n```\n`=` underline - this is probably h2 in this document.\n\n```\n仕様\n==========\n```\n`=` underline - also h2.\n\n```\n内部構造・改修時の留意点\n============================================\n```\n`=` underline - also h2.\n\nIn RST, heading levels are determined by the order of occurrence. The first non-overlined heading with a character determines h2. Since all subsections use `=` without overline, they're all h2 in this document's hierarchy.\n\nBut V3's rule specifically says \"RST: h2=text+------\" (using dashes). So if we're strictly following that definition, this source has no h2 sections using dashes. I think V3's definition might be simplified, and the actual intent is to check if the source has multiple major sections that should be split. There are 3 major sections here (コードサンプル, 仕様, 内部構造・改修時の留意点) all merged into s1. For the section ID check, V3 says IDs should follow sequential format like s1, s2, s3, and the knowledge file only has s1, which is fine since there's only one section. I could flag this as a potential issue since 3 source h2 sections are merged into 1 knowledge section, but it's minor and might be acceptable.\n\nLooking more carefully at V3's rule about RST: if we strictly interpret h2 as text with dashes, there are no h2 sections here, so no discrepancy to report. The sub-check about h2 with 2000+ chars and h3 existing doesn't apply since there are no h3 sections. The section structure seems acceptable for a simple widget reference page.\n\nFor V4 hints completeness, the hints cover パスワード入力ウィジェット, field:password, sample属性, maxlength, domain, readonly, disabled, nameAlias, cssClass, dataFrom, パスワードフィールド, ローカル動作, 確認画面マスク, and JSPウィジェット. The `example` attribute name appears in the attributes table but isn't explicitly listed as a hint, though this is a minor gap. Looking at the attributes table, I notice that `example` and `initialValueDesc` are notably absent from the hints, even though they're specific enough to warrant inclusion. The other missing attributes like `id` and `comment` are too generic to be significant. I should flag `example` and `initialValueDesc` as the key missing hints. Since `no_knowledge_content` is false, I can skip that validation check. So the main finding here is that V4 validation reveals a couple of specific attribute names that should be documented in the hints but aren't. Looking at the attribute table more carefully, I see there are 12 total properties listed, but the hints only cover 8 of them. The missing ones like `example` and `initialValueDesc` are specific widget attributes that should be included in a complete hints list, so I'll flag these as V4 minor issues.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14226,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14226,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ac66802-5814-47a8-84bd-442c7a561d5c","uuid":"7eee7b16-fbaa-4bf9-adee-b1aa82f2fde3"}
